Aug 30 2009 	One of the best hotel experiences we've ever had	My wife and I wanted to go to Vegas for a quick weekend getaway for our anniversary. I read the reviews on tripadvisor and was having a tough time deciding between the Wynn and the Four Seasons. I chose the Four Seasons, and boy I am so glad I did!I have stayed at my fair share of luxury hotels - Ritz Carlton, Mandarin Oriental, other Four Seasons, and I can say, without exaggeration that our experience at the Four Seasons LV was the best we've ever had.The hotel itself is not austentasious like other Vegas properties. It's subdued, but very beautiful.When we checked in, we were upgraded to suite for our anniversary. There was a lovely chocolate anniversary cake waiting for us as well. The suite was great! Plasma television, very comfortable bed and large, beautiful bathroom (Bulgari toiletries were a nice touch).Since we were there for only one night, we caught an early morning flight from SFO. We were at the hotel by 10am but check-in wasn't until 3pm. No problem, the front desk gave us access to the beautiful spa where we changed. They then held our bags while we lounged at the pool. By noon, we got a call the room was ready and our bags were taken up. Now that's service!The concierge got our great dinner and show tickets, my wife got a great massage, and the maid wished us a happy anniversary when she showed up for turn-down service.The brunch is not one of those huge Vegas chow-down sessions. It's was smaller, but the quality more than made up for it.And even though we had to check out by 11am, the hotel again held our bags while we sat by the pool. We used the spa again to shower and change and we were off to the airport for our late afternoon flight.If you are thinking of going to Vegas and can't decide which luxury property to stay it - do yourself a favor and pick the Four Seasons.	
