Aug 25 2009 	Top notch	The Four Seasons Las Vegas is a beautiful hotel with extremely impressive service and very friendly staff. I have previously stayed at the Bellagio and as a hotel the Four Seasons far surpasses this in terms of luxury and comfort.Arrival and check-in was amazing, bags efficiently whisked off, two people to open the doors, and we were personally escorted by a very friendly doorman to the queueless check-in desks and introduced there by name. The receptionist (Cara) was exceptional and was genuinely warm and welcoming and we instantly felt like valued guests. We were lucky enough to be given a great upgrade to a beautiful suite, and recieved several genuine apologies that there would be a delay getting it ready for us (this delay was a grand total of 4 minutes 10 seconds!). Incredible! The standard of service at the hotel continued to be exemplary for the remainder of our stay. Concierge service was excellent and they always went the extra mile. The suite, needless to say, was beautiful and enormous. The bed was easily the most comfortable we have ever slept on, with amazing sheets and the softest pillows. Turn down was excellent every night, with water by the bed, slippers and robes laid out, and all the towels in the bathroom replaced. Housekeeping was always exemplary. All the furnisings in the room were clearly very high quality and the decoration was very tasteful. There were two huge HDTVs in our room, each with a DVD player. The pool area is lovely, and each guest is escorted to there chosen sunlounger which they make up for you with soft white towels. Ice-water was always promptly delivered. The two jacuzzis were lovely and always quiet. Excellent pool service as has previously been described. We went to the Mandalay Bay pool once, which was a busy fun place and great for kids and party-people. We were definitely glad to have the Four Seasons pool to come back to though!Location is probably the worst thing about staying at this hotel - however we really didn't think its as bad as some others have made out and definitely would not put us off staying here again. The walk to the midstrip was completely manageable and actually fun (though prob not with kids). We also used the posh hotel car once which provided an excellent free service. Taxi to the Bellagio cost about $12. All the lifts at the Four Seasons stop at the Mandalay Bay casino, which is lovely and one of our top 3 on the strip. It is very easy to find the door back to the Four Seasons, it is signposted everywhere, contrary to what other reviewers have posted. You will love the immediate calm hush once you pass through it to come back to your room.All in all a fantastic hotel with true 5* service. I would recommend it to anybody.	
Aug 24 2009 	Absolutely the Best!	Hands down, this is the best hotel in Vegas. There are so many reasons why:1. Hotel is elegant, quiet, beautiful and smells great (no smoking). After visiting the other hotels and you arrive back at the Four Seasons, you feel that you are walking into peaceful bliss. You really notice the difference of the air quality and ambience in this hotel after you visit the other hotels (b/c even the other high end hotels have huge crowds, lines and smoke).2. Perfect for everyone in your group or family b/c for those who don't like all the smoke and gaming (my husband), the hotel is perfect. For those who want gaming and all the Vegas stuff (me), you just walk through a door to the Mandalay Bay. Literally, it is that easy. It is kind of like you have a door separating two different worlds. Very nice.3. Service is top notch. The staff is amazing, they cater to your every need and so pleasant through it all. They treat you as an honored guest, greet you by name and truly make you feel at home. They must train their staff rigorously b/c everyone was so professional, polite and service oriented. It was refreshing to see that excellent service still exists in this day and age.4. Pool is awesome - great service, great temperature and respectful guests (we went swimming at Mandalay Bay as well and many of the guests were rude and loud - lots of posturing going on). My husband and sons swam at Mandalay Bay for only 20 minutes (even with the wave pool, lazy river, etc.). They said the water was too cold, too many people. They had so much more fun at the Four Seasons pool - go figure.5. Great room service and restaurant (Verandah) - the food is quite good here and very child friendly. The weekend breakfast buffet is good. Not the biggest selection compared to the Vegas buffets, but the quality is superb. Personally, I prefer a smaller selection with excellent food than a big selection with ok food. Again, great service.6. Kids are made to feel so welcome here. When we arrived at our room, my two sons were greeted in the entry foyer with a plate filled with a chocolate puzzle, M&amp;M's and gummy bears (for each of them). The plates had their names written in chocolate. In the bath, their names were spelled out with lettered sponges and they each received their own child-friendly shower kit. There were even child robes for each of them. They also provided very comfy slippers to wear in the room and my kids loved them (even if they were meant for the adults). My 7 year old son stated that this was the best hotel ever!7. Valet - friendly staff. Whenever they brought our car, there were two chilled water bottles in the car and they always asked if we needed directions.There really is no reason to stay at any other hotel in Vegas. You have the best of both worlds here b/c it is just a door away from Mandalay Bay. We will always stay at this hotel when we are in Vegas.	
