Aug 21 2009 	Very Nice Indeed	Entering the Four Seasons is so different from entering any other hotel on the Strip. It is peaceful and calm and there are no slot machines.Check in was quick and friendly with no delays. The room was delightful, spacious and comfortable with a large bathroom (separate bath and shower) with L'Occitane toiletries.The floors the Four Seasons uses are obviously part of the Mandalay Bay tower, as the layout is immediately recognisable, but that's not a bad thing.The only con, if it is one, is that the elevators are quite a walk from reception. As the rooms are in Mandalay Bay really you need to go that distance in order to line up with that building. You also need to be aware that you are right at the bottom of the Strip, so if you want to see the Ballagio fountains or the Star Trek exhibition at the Hilton etc it's a very long walk.I didn't use any of the facilities, only having time to sleep and shower but overall this is a very nice and comfortable hotel and an oasis of calm amidst the mad glittering neon of Vegas.	
Aug 20 2009 	loved it.	Four Seasons Hotel in Las Vegas? That was my initial reaction as I had never seen the hotel. That is because it is an hotel within a hotel!The Four Seasons takes up the top floors of the Mandalay Bay hotel block. The only sign for the hotel is an entrance sign on Las Vegas Boulevard South near the Mandalay Bay Conference Center.The lobby is on the ground floor and unlike other strip hotels it does not have a casino nor a parking garage. There is easy access direct into the Mandalay Bay casino, and if you don't want to use the valet parking ($19/ night) you can park in Mandalay Bay.The Four Seasons is a great place to stay if you want to be in Vegas but avoid the full on Blitz of casino noise and bustle every time you leave your room to go anywhere. You can easily come and go without seeing a casino area. But there is easy access via a room key controlled door directly into the Mandalay bay casino.The pool at the hotel is great. The pool is on the ground floor and fenced off and although it gets busy it does not feel as packed as other pools in Vegas. Service at the pool is outstanding, they set up your beds, you can order food, they bring round jugs of ice water all the time, bring round small smoothies, popsicles and iced fruit. If you want it is a short walk to the Mandalay Wave pool and pools. The pool at the hotel tend to be mostly adults.The service overall is what makes the hotel so good. There is a lot of attention to detail everywhere. The room cleaning is meticulous and they take time to sort and tidy your toiletries even! In the excellent (and quiet) fitness room they check if you want a drink as you work out. Overall the four seasons make you feel like a guest, not just a number.As the hotel is at the end of the strip you also feel a bit out of the madness. But as there is a tram that runs every 5 minutes to Excalibur you can get to the strip fast. But is a long walk to places like Caesar’s palace, so cabs or a car is a good idea.The rooms are a good size and comfortable. We chose a strip view which I highly recommend as you get a stunning view both in the day and especially at night. As the hotel takes the top 4 floors all are great. We were on the top floor (39th) which was amazing.It is worth watching the four seasons site for promotions, we got 3 nights for the price of 2 which is a great deal. It is also best to try and stay in Vegas and the hotel in the week if you can, as it is clearly quieter and even the casino at Mandalay bay, restaurants are quieter - and less drunk and loud weekend partying crowds!	
Aug 20 2009 	4 1/2 stars great hotel!	This was my first visit to a Four Season's and I could not beat the deals they were offering. Buy 2 nights and get one free made the trip very affordable and I was not going to pass on the opportunity to stay in this beautifal hotel. The location is very nice - secluded, and away from the congestion of the mid-Strip. The walk to the other hotels was long at times and hot (in the 100s) but doable and good exercise.The hotel is very clean and very quiet, everyone was very friendly and willing to help as much as possible. The room is small but well-appointed with nce bathroom, robes, toiletries. We had an airport view which I loved - very relaxing watching the planes take off from McCarran Int'l.The pool was my favorite part - shaded, secluded and quiet - so nice! We got great chairs which they clean for you and lay a towel down. They come over often to ask if you need anything. The water was perfect temperature and the pool and hottubs were very clean. Also loved the workout facility and gym spa.We ate at the restaurants in Mandalay Bay - Red Square and China Grill. With the recession, the prices in most of the restaurants have been cut which now makes them a great deal - especially if eating early. Both restuarants were fantastic.The only problem with the hotel and the reason it is 4 1/2 stars instead of 5 is with the concierge. I emailed the concierge 2 times before arriving at the hotel and never received a response. When I was there, they were not the most helpful. I had one minor complaint about some room service and the concierge apologized and said she would take care of it, but nothing happened. With only that minor problem, the hotel was close to perfect and I would definitely stay here again!	
