Jun 25 2009 	Good but could have been better	The Four Seasons Las Vegas is a haven for those that want to get away for a few hours from the overkill of casino's, noise, heat and people.Tucked away on the side of the Mandelay Bay hotel it is capable to give you the look and feel of relaxed quality.The service is good to excellent at reception, the swimming pool and breakfast.The rooms are spacious, well furnished and have all that one needs. A remark though is that, where one gets free WIFI connections all over the States in RV parks, hotels, café's etc, this hotel charges $14.99 for a one day connection. In a world where communication is the standard and no longer an option and in a expensive hotel such as this one the WIFI should be free.One other remark is that the noise from 35 floors down comes into the room. Unfortunately only double glasing was used and this could have been better.The swimming pool is too small for the amount of people using it. Four Season quality involves enough space in and around the swimming pool with soft music making the stay at the pool more enjoyable. In our case there were hardly any free spaces and the pop/rock music may blend in well with Las Vegas but, to me, was too loud and not at all relaxing.Other than that this is a great hotel and again, compared to the rest of Vegas, a heaven on earth.	
