Mar 16 2009 	Best customer service and comfort in Las Vegas	We just returned from our first stay at the Four Seasons Las Vegas and it will not be our last. From beginning to end the entire staff treated us to the most amazing customer service we have ever experienced. Luggage was in our room before we turned the key in the door. No long lines to check in. No casino bling or congestion. A quiet and classy lobby with a safe and relaxing haven from the crazy LV blvd. world. We were addressed by name in the restaurants here and with each phone call to front desk, service employees, bell captains etc. The room was very clean and comfortable with wonderful city views. The beds are beyond description. It was one of the best nights sleep ever. With all the other high end hotels on the strip, most offer nice accommodations but with the thousands of rooms and people to service you will never get the personal touch that this hotel can offer. Hallways were clean day and night, elevators swift upon call, pool area and spa both quiet and relaxing. You can get to Mandalay Bay easily if you want to transition to the casino environment. My only negative comments would be that this hotel is very close to the airport, so depending on the wing where your room is located you will hear some jet noise at times. It is also at the far end of the strip with only close walking access to Lexor and Excalibur. You will need to use taxi, car or trams to get to other hotels. These factors will not keep us away, as this gem of a hotel is the best on the strip if you want to be treated like a respectful paying guest and not just a room number...	
Mar 11 2009 	Hospitality from personnel was wonderful	As a Texas girl visiting the western United States, I never know what type of service I am going to get. There are times that the services can be haughty and lacking in the genuine personalization I am used to getting in my southern state. The Four Seasons Las Vegas more than exceeded my expectations. The staff was welcoming, and treated me like a person rather than a commodity. My husband and I were visiting Las Vegas for the first time for our 20th wedding anniversary. We arrived to receive a delectable chocolate mouse cake with &quot;Happy Anniversary&quot; beautifully writen on it. We were also going to be picking up a new puppy while visiting the area, and the Four Seasons went above and beyond to lay out a doggy bed, bowls, and treats to wecome our newest family member. Our first night I also ordered room service by phone from a very cheery attendant. She was also more than helpful with my wine requests. The room service arrived prompty with a smile and a waiter that was also more than helpful with information about the food and wine. After we dined, all I had to do was make a phone call and someone came and picked up the table and dishes. Great service!As a topper, when we were leaving the hotel I forgot some jewelry on the glass above the sink. I asked the front desk clerk at check out and he quickly called security and within minutes my jewelry was delivered to me in the lobby while I sipped my morning tea. I will definitely be looking forward to my next stay at the Four Seasons Las Vegas!	
