vice. We had booked the bed &amp; breakfast package which is a $59 credit towards your breakfast in the room or in the Veranda restaurant. We ordered breakfast in the room which arrived promptly. The food was well presented, hot &amp; delicious. Upon checking out, the breakfast was not on the bill so I told them I would expect the charge to appear later on my credit card. The receptionist returned my credit card and I said Thanks and walked away. No printout was given to me. So I still do not know how much I paid for the night. Outside the hotel we asked for a cab to the airport &amp; they kindly took us to the airport in their courtesy car. I found the bellmen, driver &amp; room service staff to be helpful &amp; courteous but would not book this Four Seasons again as I was expecting something to warrant the TripAdvisor number 1 rating and could not find it.	
