Sep 25 2008 	A Sanctuary Amidst the Chaos	We just returned from a 4 day stay during which we married at one of the local chapels. This resort is exactly as represented – a perfect respite from the Vegas madness. The service is top-notch with extreme attention to detail. The rooms are beautifully appointed and cleaned several times a day, yet the maids are rarely ever seen. We worked out in the incredible gym (best hotel gym I’ve ever seen) and our room was already cleaned by the time we returned at 9.30 or 10 am. The view down the strip (we had room 36131) was incredible. The pool is excellent, if a bit undersized. The service at the pool was also excellent. The concierge desk was outstanding and highly informative. They arranged dinner reservations, show tickets, golf and other things and did so with consistent enthusiasm and grace. They followed up to see if we enjoyed ourselves at the events they had arranged. At one point, we arranged a town car to take us to the courthouse to fill out the marriage application (a few days before the wedding). The car was 15 minutes late and when I notified the concierge about the late arrival (we had another appointment later that day and were pressed for time), they comp’d the town car, a $75 expense, and I hadn’t even asked them to do so. The senior concierge said, this is the Four Seasons Las Vegas, and if it’s not perfect, then there is no charge!” This was just typical of the incredible service this hotel provides. We also had spa services, which were outstanding as well and the spa itself is lovely. We are not huge fans of Vegas overall and this was our first trip to Vegas and we went specifically to get married and to enjoy this hotel. We will probably return just because we loved this hotel so much and, or course, because we were married in Vegas!	
