Aug 31 2008 	Not perfect but most likely one of the top hotels in the USA.	I have stayed in this hotel multiple times. On my recent check in, the hotel informed me that they cancelled my reservation, and that they were full. When I requested both the Hotel General manager, and called american express they did relent, and charge my Amex and give me an upgraded room. However, as Amex had zero record of declining anything, and the hotel didn't have any record of contacting anyone, I'd reccomend anyone with reservations call the hotel the day of arrival and make sure someone didn't screw something up.Beyond this, this is truly adult fantasy land. Any request that you would make (as long as it's legal) would most likely be acted with pleasure. My wife was talking in the pool, saying that it was unusual to be thirsty standing in a pool of water. Within 3 mins, there was a glass of icewater in her hands. The rooms are a similar layout to the Mandalay bay, but the place is immaculate, the &quot;Magic&quot; icebucket is almost always cold and full. The Spa is small but extremely nice, and the Verandah is on par with just about any restaruant in Las Vegas. (Breakfast, Lunch or Dinner)Pet Friendly.	
