Aug 25 2008 	Wonderful Hidden Gem	We originally chose the Four Seasons because it was the only dog friendly hotel that was of high standards but ended up not bringing our dog when we found out you can not leave your animal unattended in the room alone as they will come and bring your pet down to a cage while you are out. Although our little dog would have been perfectly fine lounging in the luxurious room while we were out, we did not want to break any hotel rules and opted to leave her at home. I am also sure the care she would have received would of been of high standards given all of the staff we encountered working here. After I read all of the reviews we still opted for the Four Seasons over the Wynn, Bellagio and the Venician and I am glad we did!Getting away from the noise and hustle and bustle is so nice even in Vegas. Service doesn't get any better. Upon arrival we had a cake in our room as it was our anniversary week. All service and food was wonderful and our strip view room was spotless and cozy. You never wait in lines like other hotels for check in/out, cabs or concierge duties. We walked over to Mandalay pools twice and turned around immediately realizing there was no service, no shade, no comfortable chairs and no quiet. Although the Four Seasons pool area was crowded each day, I always found a chair. I understand they are expanding the deck so more people will be able to be poolside. There is only seating for 100 and they told us there is a wait list to have a lounge chair at the pool in high season. Although, once you have established your lounging seats expect the finest service ever...cold towels, pitchers of iced-lemon water, popsicles, fresh fruit, cucumbers for the eyes, face misting, eye glass cleaning, magazines....service, service, service but never did it once feel over the top like I was being huddled over or bothered like many other 5 star properties. These servers have it down pat!The spa and gym are fabulous and the gym and locker room come as complimentary even if you do not use the spa. It is loaded up with ammenaties and state of the art equipment. The showers are excellent. You may not use your own hoel room to shower! I had six different spa treatments and all were wonderful! Heather was a fabulous massage therapist and I wish I could remember the other therapists names, they were all good. The rooms were cozy and pristine.The Verandah restaurant was wonderful for breakfast and the server Leo deserves major praise. He remembered things you liked and desired from other visits....what a memory, what excellent service he provided! Each day was a wonderful experience.Getting to the casino is a breeze, Mandalay has a lot of play just downstairs but hop in a cab for action down the street if you desire more. Also a tram will take you right to New York New York and the MGM. It really is not out of the way to go to other hotels like previously mentioned reviews. At most hotels you would use cab service for going to other strip locations anyway, especially in 107 degree weather. It boggles my mind that people complain that this hotel is out of the way. The sushi bar in the MGM is great and the Italian restaurant in the Venician is excellent. I do not remember the names. The only restaurant we were not crazy about was Shanghai in Mandalay Bay. Service was not up to par and the food was rather blah and boring for that type of restaurant. Decor was lovely however. The Four Seasons Charlie Parker restaurant was closed for renovations, otherwise we would have tried it also.I found myself retiring early to the comfort of my Four Seasons bed and hotel room nightly while my husband played into the wee hours of the morning. There is something for everyone here. There is definitely a reason why this hotel is rated number one. I guess it really isn't a secret! We will be back.	
