Aug 6 2008 	Undeniably Vegas' Best Hotel	We have been taking our annual pilgrimage to Las Vegas for the past 12 years and have finally found the crown jewel hotel. We have stayed at almost every premium hotel up and down the strip and the level of comfort and service is unparalleled with what you receive at the Four Seasons. For example, if you hang out at the pool, you receive continuous free water, popsicles, sunglass cleanings, Evian water face mistings and timely visits by the poolside staff for your beverage orders. The pool is for exclusive use of the Four Seasons guests which means you don't have to get to the pool as soon as it opens for a chair. You can also use Mandalay Bay's wave pool or the Moorea Beach Club (topless sunbathing) if you choose, although Moorea is not free admittance. The hotel is peaceful in that there is no noise from kids running up and down the hallways at night like many of the other strip hotels. The casino and hotel lobby are reachable through three Four Seasons only elevators. On the surface, this doesn't seem like a big deal, but wait until you see the lines at Mandalay Bay or The Hotel to use an elevator. People in Mandalay's casino were complaining of a twenty minute wait just to get onto an elevator. And worse yet, an one hour line to check-in. We waited two minutes to check into the hotel and no wait to check-out. Everything in the Mandalay complex can be charged to your Four Seasons room as well (e.g. restaurants, bars, lounges, etc.). The conceirge can get you a reservation at almost any restaurant on short notice and even got us access into the Foundation Room on Saturday evening for no charge (Foundation Room is a private nightclub atop Mandalay Bay). As we told the front desk on check-out, we have now found our new home in Las Vegas!	
