Jul 3 2008 	except the pool in the afternoon serenity found in las vegas!!!	here's the pros and cons (very few cons)pros: staff and service excellent. discreet location within mandalay bay fantastic. room amenities plush. hardly any wait at all for a cab. (if you've stayed at any major strip hotel you know what i'm talking about on a saturday night - this hotel has about a 1-2 min wait for a cab). ability to use mandalay pool which is crazy, crazy. proximity to everything mandalay has to offer (14 restaurants). we had a north facing strip view which was fantastic. nice gym with tvs on the cardio equipment, bottled water, gatorade and great service by staff. spa looked nice but did not use it, but could smell the eucalyptus (ahhhh!) as you walk to the elevator. great concierge. absolutely no smell of smoke anywhere, instead it's eucalyptus and some kind of gardenia-type of flower which i call the &quot;four seasons lobby smell.&quot; fantastic pool side service - frozen popsicles, evian spritzers, sunglasses personally cleaned, ice water pitchers and those very comfortable padded lounge chairs with those oversized, perfectly fitting towels draped over them. and now for the cons: pool itself is a nice size, but pool area (where the lounge chairs are) is on the smaller side. we thought we'd be able to hide away, but not. the chairs are right next to each other. no cabana rentals due to small area around pool. pool and two jacuzzis close at 7pm which we thought was absolutely ridiculous. mandalay also closes at 7. the location is at the southernmost of the strip hotels definitely not near the center of the &quot;action.&quot; extremely dull and boring shopping at the mandalay bay and only a gift shop at the four seasons. if we were staying only a fri-sun, we would stay elsewhere because of the location. next to the mandalay bay is luxor and excalibur. across the street from excalibur is mgm, new york and tropicana. a very dull, to say the least, corner of hotels. too bad they couldn't have placed the 4 seasons and/or mandalay bay closer to wynn, venetian or the mall. also, too bad the four seasons couldn't have been a standalone hotel so that the pool area could have been more spread out. we also didn't like the size of the room and bathroom. if you're used to a larger four seasons room you will be disappointed. contrary to another review re the closet size - our room had two closets that were opened with double doors. they were definitely not &quot;walk-in&quot; type of closets. the bathroom, although plush, is on the small side. it does have a separate shower, sink and toilet area, but is smaller than the other four seasons we've stayed at. also there is no adult pool. in the early afternoon, the families come back to the four seasons after they've had it at the mandalay pool. that's when the noise and such starts up. if you're looking for adultness you have to hit the adult pool at mandalay, &quot;moorea.&quot; we didn't go there because it is definitely a long walk and in the 112 heat did not seem appealing. we would return to the hotel, but only if longer than a couple of days. in any case, thanks again four seasons for a nice stay.	
