Apr 22 2008 	Quiet Las Vegas Hotel	The Four Seasons Hotel in Las Vegas is a quiet retreat. If this is what you are looking for then this is your place. If you are looking for a little more excitement then stay more in the heart of the strip. The Four Seasons does not have a casino but is connected to the Mandalay Bay Resort, so you can have the best of both worlds. It was nice to enjoy the Mandalay Bay pools and then when they got crowded retreat to the peace and quiet and attentive service at the Four Seasons.  My husband and I spent four nights at the Four Seasons in April. We had great weather and took advantage of the pool all four days. The service at the pool was good, but the least consistent with other Four Seasons that we have stayed at. Most of the staff was extremely attentive and always called you by name, others were not as good. The front desk and the bellmen were excellent. The concierge did a great job getting us dinner reservations and transportation. Even when we had a problem with are final bill the front desk handled it very well. The rooms were clean and well kept, the amenities very nice.  If you are looking to escape the craziness of Las Vegas, stay here.	
