Jul 12 2007 	Construction Noise 	If you're thinking about staying at the Four Seasons any time soon, be warned. The construction noise from the Mandalay Bay Hotel (floors below) travels up to even the top floor of the Four Seasons (where we were staying). During our vacation, the jack-hammering would begin between 7 a.m. and 9 a.m. and would extend, intermittently, until 5 p.m. This was not exactly the relaxing stay which we had expected, and the Four Seasons' staff did not appear to care about the situation. In fact, we got the feeling that they were tired of hearing guests repeatedly complain. However, with the Four Seasons' reputation, and the prices charged for the rooms, we certainly expected a wonderful experience, and we were quite dismayed by our treatment.Another disappointing aspect of our stay was the terrible front desk staff. The women at the front desk/reception, in particular, were unfriendly, demeaning and snobby. They give you far less than a &quot;five star&quot; welcome.On the positive side of things, the pool service was top-notch, and the breakfast at the Verandah restaurant was outstanding. Beyond those two &quot;high points,&quot; we fail to see what makes this property an oasis in the desert. We have had better experiences at Caesar's Palace!So, it's a mixed bag at the Four Season, but we certainly would not recommend anyone booking this property, at least until the construction at Mandalay Bay is complete.Happy travels!	
