Jul 4 2007 	Good hotel but average by FS standards	The primary advantage of FS Las Vegas is not its rooms which are almost the same as the adjoining Mandalay Bay hotel, nor its pool, which is tiny compared to others, but its calm quiet environment. It is a refuge compared to the riotous bustle of the other large hotels.At check in, there was no one in line and we were checked in quickly and efficiently. Upon learning that we had no bags we needed help with, the receptionist walked us half way to the elevator banks and it was self service from there. I found that a bit odd. Definitely not like other FS properties.We had the Mountain or otherwise the full Monty airport view with a side way glance towards the Strip. Because FS is at the top of Mandalay Bay, even a 'cheap' view affords better views than most regular hotels. The room was standard FS and came with a flat screen TV.What is worth recommending is the breakfast at the Veranda restaurant. A simple corn beef hash with eggs takes on a new meaning when it is executed to perfection. And you have the benefit of outdoor seating near the pool.Yes, the FS pool is small and quiet if that is what you want, although you won't escape the music blaring from the nearby Mandalay pool club. But the Mandalay Bay pool area is worth checking out if no other reason than to people watch and enjoy the wave pool.Overall, there was nothing spectacular about FS Las Vegas although I might try staying next time at more central properties like the Venetian if nothing else than to save myself from walking a lot in the 110 degree heat.	
