Apr 14 2007 	An Oasis of Calm	The Four Seasons Las Vegas offers a wonderful, comfortable stay for those that need a bit of calm and relaxation. Located atop the Mandalay Bay, the hotel has a separate entrance, Lobby, restaurants and facilities. You will be whisked away into a tranquil, luxurious world- the perfect foil to the otherwise hectic pace of Vegas. Gamblers should note that this property does not have a casino, but you can easily access the sprawling gaming floor of Mandalay Bay.Rooms are pretty much what you would expect from the Four Seasons. While not as large as some of the mini-suite accommodations offered elsewhere in Vegas, you will have all the usual comforts like mini-bar, marble bathrooms with robes, and exquisite L'Occitane toiletries. Decor is rather dated, a la early 90's luxury with a tropical twist, but that should not deter you. Try and splurge on a Strip View Room, or politely ask for an upgrade upon check-in (there may well be an extra charge, but it is worth it!).The hotel boasts its' own lovely pool area, much quieter than those found at the mega-resorts. Adjacent to the pool is a small but well-equipped exercise room (free of charge unlike most hotels of this caliber), as well as a soothing Spa. Treatments are fine though a bit expensive.Staff here are eager to please- we were constantly being offered complimentary use of the comfortable chauffered sedan (please tip the driver generously ). When we had a noise-related problem (see below) in our original room, we were moved to an enormous, beautifully appointed One Bedroom Suite complete with a jaw-dropping view all the way up the Strip. We had a full bath plus a large powder room near the front door, a wonderful living room area with adjacent office nook, and a large bedroom with many closets and that awesome view right from the king-size bed. We were also offered complimentary treats which arrived periodically out of the blue.....the chocolate-covered almonds were heavenly. We loved the fact that this hotel is one of the only that welcomes dogs and met several pampered pooches in the elevators. Some pets even have their own engraved dishes awaiting them upon arrival (those which are lucky enough to stay here regularly). On site are a cafe, a fine Steak House, and a seasonal poolside cafe as well as a lounge. Guests have signing privileges at a myriad of other eateries throughout the vast Mandaly Bay / THE Hotel complex....you can also try one of the other Spas.The only problem we encountered was that when we arrived back in our original room on the first night (Monday), we discovered that above us was an all-night party complete with live dj's playing directly above us. The problem stems from the fact that above the Four Seasons are the High-Roller Suites of Mandalay Bay, and also a popular nightclub operated by House of Blues. On Mondays the entire floor becomes a wild party open to the public. By all means, if staying over a Monday, do NOT stay on the top floor of the Four Seasons (Floor 39 if memory serves). I should mention that the problem was rectified beyond our wildest dreams (see above), and that the Front Desk staff assured us they had never had similar complaints.Staying here was an absolute joy in every other respect, and we cannot say enough good things about this fine property and its' incredible staff. We also enjoyed being connected through a discreet secured door to the fun chaos of the Mandalay Bay, yet having a wonderful oasis of calm and tranquility to go to when we had had enough noise and action.I should also mention that the other usual touches one would expect from a Four Seasons stay are also here.....fine food, great service and masses of fresh flowers.There is talk of the Four Seasons eventually opening a new Resort adjacent to one of the other Strip resorts. Perhaps this particular property could use a bit of freshening-up here and there, but all in all this was one of our best hotel stays ever and is highly recommended, especially if you are fortunate enough to afford a stay in one of the palatial suites. Splurge if you can, you will not be disappointed!	
Apr 10 2007 	Dignified Las Vegas? You've arrived.	Las Vegas has made every attempt to lure travelers to their ever so vibrant resorts and casinos. You will find a variety of tastes among hotels, but no hotel delivers a more dignified experience than the Four Seasons Las Vegas.Unique to this hotel, is its prime location, with few inconveniences often associated with most Las Vegas Hotels and Resorts. The Four Seasons Las Vegas is housed within the Mandalay Bay Resort and Casio, occupying floors 35-39 of this mega resort. The Four Seasons however acts as its own property, with a separate hotel entrance, restaurant facilities, pool area, spa etc. If you never left the hotel itself, you might be hard pressed to realize you were actually in Las Vegas. All Four Seasons guests have access to the Mandalay Bay Resort through several different private access doors. These access areas offer Four Seasons guest the ability to quickly walk to casino areas, shopping and other popular areas of Mandalay Bay. What's nice however is that you never have to see a casino, if you choose not to, when staying at the FS Las Vegas.The level of service was beyond impeccable, in every regard. Our every need was anticipated, met, and exceeded at all times throughout our stay. We had two connecting rooms, in the Deluxe Category, which offered views of the &quot;Strip&quot; I would however recommend choosing a mountain view, as there are less lights, and a nice view of the pool area. Rooms were classic Four Seasons in style, with extremely comfortable beds and luxurious furnishings. Since this hotel was originally opened, the rooms have been updated to reflect a more contemporary motif. The bathrooms were stocked with an abundance of amenities, along with a seamless glass shower and separate soaking tub.The Verandah restaurant was superb on every occasion. I would highly recommend the breakfast and lunch service. The pool and spa were fantastic, again offering a more private Las Vegas pool experience. You don't get the sense of overcrowding, and the level of service is in line with the rest of the hotel. The fitness center is also first class, featuring a variety of advanced machines.If your travel plans call for business or leisure, and you desire a peaceful stay, you will be delighted with the Four Seasons Las Vegas. Expect service and quality that rivals that of the competition. You won't find a better hotel in Las Vegas.	
