Jan 21 2007 	First time and it was a charm!	This was our first stay at the Four Seasons in Las Vegas, and we knew it would be nice since it was a 5-star, 5-diamond hotel but we were impressed even beyond what we were expecting! We have been faithful Bellagio goers for years but we have a new addition to the family (a puppy!) that we wanted to take with us and the Four Seasons is the only hotel on the strip that takes animals.They took great care of everything, including our dog. My only complaint was that they were to have a doggy pack ready for him when we got to the hotel but they brought it up later that night when we ordered room service for him. Yes - for the dog! They will make anything you want, even cut it up into the appropriate-size pieces. They give you nice ceramic bowls, Evian water and a little kit that includes plastic bags for accidents. They also had a nanny service they contracted that would watch children or pets, and we enjoyed our nanny (ask for Nancy if you have a small animal!) so much we invited her back each night of our stay. It was a bit pricy but worth it if you are afraid your pet will cry or bark if you aren't there. They do have a policy that if anyone hears your animal barking, they will be removed from your room and put in the maid's area until you return to the hotel, and you will be charged $50, so paying a bit more for someone to watch them is worth it.Other than the excellent way they treated our pet, they treated us well also. They got us into every club, restaurant and show we wanted and made sure we always had the best tables and seats. They had very comfortable beds, impeccably cleaned rooms, huge plasma televisions and L'Occitane products in the bath that were just lovely. Turndown service every evening and they will clean the room any time, 24 hours a day, depending on your sleeping schedule. Room service was always delivered within half an hour, hot food with a smiling waiter ready to take care of anything you need. We did not encounter one rude employee our entire stay, everyone from the concierge to the bellhops were professional and warm. We will definitely be returning!	
