Oct 17 2006 	Extremely Lovely	My husband and I stayed 6 nights at the Four Seasons Hotel in Las Vegas as my husband attended a conference held at the Mandelay Bay Convention Center. I am a real stickler for good customer service, and I am so pleased to say that the staff at The Four Seasons could NOT have been more pleasant. We had such a lovely time there. The room was spotless and very comfortable. We had 2 parcels delivered from out of town during our stay and they were delivered to our room in a timely manner. Every staff member we had contact with was friendly, knowledgeable and professional. The housekeeping staff was top notch - very attentive to the room and very thoughtful with the turndown service. Each evening our bed was turned down, lights dimmed - and soft music and lovely video's of nature were tuned in on the very large plasma television awaiting our return to the hotel. The concierge was helpful to arrange meals, suggest restaurants, give directions and arrange transportation. The staff was truly friendly, from the General Manager to the kind man who was busily painting miniscule scuff marks on the baseboards in the hallway. Room service was wonderful and extremely prompt. The meals we enjoyed were all perfectly prepared. The fresh flowers and special touches to room service did not go unnoticed. The valet service was very nice. The staff was attentive and professional. I made special notice that all staff members addressed us by name whenever they could. Our name is pronounced differently than the spelling looks, and it was so refreshing to have our name pronounced correctly. Again - small touches matter. &quot;Thoughtful&quot; would be the word I would use to sum up our experience at the Four Seasons. Yes, the hotel is very pretty, the rooms are well appointed, the lobby is comfortable and well decorated...but is was truly the people at the Four Seasons who made our stay so very pleasant. The staff seemed sincerely interested in our comfort. It was so refreshing to have such a lovely experience. So many times we stay at beautiful hotels with nice rooms -- but the staff lacks something. Perhaps they are snooty, too busy to attend to their guests or maybe just unhappy in their jobs...It makes a GRAND difference in the experience that the traveler has. Many hotels are lovely, but we would never patronize them again purely because of the ill-mannered staff. The Four Seasons was the antithesis of a hotel with a poorly trained or organized staff. No matter where we stay from now on, my husband and I will forever hold hotel experiences up against The Four Seasons in Las Vegas...It will be extremely hard for a hotel to measure up!	
Oct 9 2006 	Fabulous Four Seasons	I researched Las Vegas Hotels in depth using this website before deciding to stay at the Four Seasons, with two children aged 4 and 6 we really wanted a high quality, quiet, smoke free environment. Check in was effortless, the lobby was beautifully appointed. Our room was exactly what we booked, two double beds facing away from the strip. We were celebrating our 20th wedding anniversary (it fell at the end of our 3 week US holiday) and we were pleased to find that the hotel had left a dessert in our room with a congratulatory note. There were separate desserts for our children plus special bath products for them (which they loved). The room was very spacious and the bathroom was huge, with high quality toiletries. Housekeeping was excellent. We ate at the Verandah restaurant twice, delicious meals both times and a reasonably priced childrens' menu. The pool was everything that other reviewers have outlined - wonderful service, pristine environment. Our kids loved it and after a visit to the crowded Mandalay Bay wave pool couldn't wait to return to the more relaxed atmosphere at the Four Seasons. We had easy access to the Mandalay Bay casino, buffet etc which allowed us to have the Vegas experience. We visited a lot of other casinos and even at the more expensive locations witnessed long check out queues, masses of people milling around the lobby etc. We were thrilled with our 4 night stay at the Four Seasons and very sad to say goodbye.	
