Oct 1 2006 	Amazing experience at Four Seasons	My wife and I just returned from our honeymoon in Las Vegas. Our decision to stay at the Four Seasons was the best decision made about our trip. The hotel is truly wonderful. The staff's attention to detail is second to none. I arranged to have a limo pick us up at the airport (through the conceirge at Four Seasons). Our flight was delayed getting into Vegas, and the driver was waiting for us right when we got down to baggage claim. He was a great guy telling us stories about some celebrities he picked up earlier. He waited patiently with us to get our bags and grabbed the all off the carousel. Then took us on a nice drive down the strip to extend our limo drive since the hotel is very close to the airport.Upon arrival at the Four Season, we were welcomed by every staff member and told congratulations for our marriage. The front desk staff was great. They offered us bottled water while checking us in, gave us a brief tour of the hotel and showed us to the elevators. We booked a Premier Strip view room. They gave us a room on the 39th floor (the top floor) with the most stunning view of the strip we've ever seen. We had champagne, flowers waiting for us in the room. The bell hop then offered us a reservation in the Foundation Room for Sunday evening (it's private alll nights except Monday). He called someone on the room phone and we were all set to arrive there at 10pm that evening. Our was great. There are much larger rooms available in Vegas, but the quality I doubt could be easily surpassed. Everything was immaculate. The bed/pillows was one of the most comfortable we've ever slept on. After sharing some champagne, we cleaned up and headed out to explore Mandalay Bay.Upon arriving back in the room later in the day, we were surprised to see that the staff had left a chocolate mouse cake with &quot;Happy Honeymoon&quot; written on it and a very nice card.The Foundation Room is very cool. The view of the strip is the best I've seen from anywhere in Vegas. The staff gave us a tour of all the private rooms and told us stories about Britney Spears and other celebrities that frequent the Foundation Room. Great time if you can get in on a day other than Monday. The pool is great. Yes, it's not huge, but who cares. The pool staff lays out towels and seat covers on your chosen chairs. They bring a pitcher of ice water when you first sit down. They come around with popcicles, Evian water sprtiz, they clean your sunglasses, bring watermelon, offer you cocktails, food. If you decide to go into the pool, they will lay down a towel on the side of the pool for you to rest your arms on so you don't burn them on the hot ground. Christopher (a pool employee) was great and we instantly connected with him as he was from our hometown. He made every pool trip a great experience. We went over to the Manadalay Beach once, but left after 30min as we couldn't stand the crowds and wanted to back in the tranquil environment of the Four Seasons. The Mandalay Beach reminded me of a water park like Water World or something - great if you are maybe with a group of friends that like to party or kids that want to play in the wave pool. The housekeepers truly earn their money at the Four Seasons. Our room was cleaned twice daily. Once in the morning and once in the evening for turndown service. If we left clothes on the floor, they would pick them up and fold them. All of our bathroom products would be lined up neatly on the bathroom counter. They would leave chocolates and the radio on when when returned for bed in the evening.One of the best parts about staying at the Four Seasons is having access to Mandalay Bay. It was so nice to be able to go gamble, drink and experience the crazyness of the casino atmosphere, then walk through the private entrance to the Four Seasons. I would recommend the Four Seasons to anyone looking for a romantic atmophere that allows you to spend some quality time with your spouse. The Four Season just gets it when it comes to catering to their guests and making your stay a truly wonderful experience.	
