May 4 2006	All I can say is "Wow"!	This was our first visit to Four Seasons Las Vegas after having stayed at all the high end properties in Vegas (with the exception of Wynn) over the last few years. By far, this property has the best that Vegas can offer.The rooms themselves were not as large or roomy as the Venetian or The Hotel at Mandalay Bay and the bathroom was also nicely put together but not outstanding. What sets this hotel apart are the facilities and the service. Since it occupies only the top four floors of Mandalay Bay, there is not a huge volume of guests that all the other mega-properties in Vegas must account for. Wherever we went, there seemed to be hotel staff who wanted to assist us. We had breakfast as part of our package and the Verandah was a lovely way to start each day. The restaurant opens onto the pool deck amidst palm trees and a waterfall. The food was excellent. When you head out to the pool, a staff member meets you and sets up your chaise lounges with towels and a fresh picture of ice water. They constantly check up on you to freshen the pitcher or hand out fresh fruit, popsicles, clean your sunglasses or spritz you with fresh Evian water. My husband and I left the secluded (and gated) confines of the 4S pool to venture out to the Mandalay Bay facilities (as a 4S guest you are allowed access to everything at Mandalay, but not vice versa). We were immediately assailed with crowds, noise and general traffic. We couldn't run back to the peaceful pool at 4S fast enough!It couldn't be easier to get to the Mandalay casino via a bank of elevators and a secured door that you must have a key to reenter. It really was the best of both worlds - the excitement of the casino and general Vegas life mixed with the serenity of a well run Four Seasons. The only thing better was the spa at Mandalay Bay versus the spa at 4S. It is much, much larger and has the best facilities of any spa on the Strip IMHO (and I've tried them all!!).From now on this will be our destination of choice in Vegas. We had a wonderful time!	
