Nov 21 2005	Average vs. Other FS	We stayed at the FS from 11/16 - 11/20 to celebrate my boyfriend's 30th b-day. The front desk and concierge staff were polite and distant (Not the type that go out of their way to make their guests feel warm and fuzzy). However, services at the pool and at the spa were excellent. Also,the food at the Verandah was delicious and priced very reasonably ($50 for 2 for breakfast). Had breakfast there every morning and are still thinking about the their french toast and truffle fries (great pool side snack for $5!). The crowd was a bit old (i.e. 40 and above) and not glamourous. All and all, the hotel lacks the energy of other high end Vegas hotels. Will most likely stay at theHotel or Wynn next time.	
Nov 8 2005	A relaxing escape	For those who have reason to be in Las Vegas but don't relish the sensory overload of the Strip, the Four Seasons is the perfect choice. The lack of a casino makes the hotel a peaceful island in the midst of the crowds. The guestroom views of the Strip and the mountains rising from the desert beyond are wonderful. The private pool is a great place to relax and read, and to enjoy the pampering provided by the pool attendants (cucumbers for the eyes, orange slices for refreshment, iced water, and evian spritzes for the face on hot days). The Verandah restaurant is a great place to start the day with brunch on a weekend morning.Best of all is the spa. The facilities, both for fitness and for pampering, are superb. The spa staff are the most friendly and helpful in the whole hotel. For those expecting perfect Four Seasons service, the hotel can be slightly disappointing. Unlike other Four Seasons, the concierges are not tops and the service is not flawless. Room service carts are left in the halls all day, and there is a constant parade of staff up and down in plain sight. It does not have the &quot;seamless service&quot; feel of other Four Seasons and other top-notch hotels.Despite this, it is still a great hotel for R&amp;R in a town that can be overwhelming at times.	
