Jul 24 2005	A Dishonest Internet Portrayal	Booked the Four Seasons with my wife, looking for a weekend getaway. The internet site portrays it as a &quot;non-gaming hotel,&quot; an &quot;oasis away from the strip&quot; and an &quot;exclusive hotel.&quot; Unfortunately, it is right on the south strip. What is worse is that, after you check in, you walk down a very long hallway, and find yourself entering the Mandalay Bay elevators. The Four Seasons in Las Vegas is simply the top four floors of the Mandalay Bay, with more expensive room rates and an &quot;exclusive pool.&quot; It was very dishonestly portrayed on the internet, and not at all worth the money. We could have had a similar room for half the price by staying two floors down. We have been fortunate to stay in many wonderful five stars hotels around the world. The Four Seasons in Las Vegas is definitely not one of them. If you really want to stay here, call them first and ask EXACTLY where there hotel is located.	
